item.description:
@exps35 wrote:

[quote=“wolfpack81, post:19, topic:189623”]http://72.14.253.104/search?q=cache:ys0063RW2tAJ:www.experts-exchange.com/Other/Puzzles_Riddles/Q_21402138.html+01000001.com&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=2&gl=us

[quote]Jchutchins:
Hey, everyone. It’s JC Hutchins, owner of 010000001.com. I wanted to make a contribution to the discussion.

First off: Thanks, willa, for dropping me a line and informing me of your post. That was very cool of you. And thanks to you guys --stengelj, Xxavier, WileE, Xestrix and SWOne – for noodling over the contents of 010000001.com, and trying to make some sense of it.

Now on to the good stuff. Based on the above replies to willa’s post, Xestrix and SWOne were/are closest to guessing the reason behind the website. 010000001.com is kinda part of a game. It’s more like a plot point, as you guys inferred. However the plot point isn’t … and won’t … be a part of a traditional game/scavenger hunt. It’s actually part of a novel that I’ve written. In my novel, our heroes are tracking the villain and are directed to a website – yeah, you guessed it: 010000001.com. There, they read instructions from the villain.

I’m currently shopping this novel to agents, in hopes of getting it published. I purchased the “real world” URL 01000001.com in the hopes that it might be visited one day by curious readers of my novel. (You know, to see if the webpage was real. I thought this would create a nice fiction-meets-reality moment for the reader; a nice little wink from me to them.) I posted the “Dear Betas” message on the site for ****s and giggles, pure self-amusement. Amazingly, willa found it waaaaay ahead of schedule! You guys have actually stumbled across an excerpt of my unpublished book. Here’s hoping my novel – tentatively titled “7th Son” – finds its way to bookshelves. Wish me luck.

In the meantime, I want you guys to know that you made my week, re: this thread. Thanks again for trying to figure out the contents of 01000001.com, and for posting your ideas. It brought a smile to my face, knowing that my insignificant webpage generated some intrigue and interest. You guys rock! Drop me a line with any q’s/comments if you wish. Take care![/quote][/quote]

I win.

sorta
